                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/18/2003&nbsp;: 12:27:01 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Re-snare timing is moderately off-topic but mentioned here so I'll comment.<br /><br />Since the last patch I have been using the dot damage on splurt as my timer.  Since the damage changes every tick it works incredibly well.  Just cast splurt immediately before or after darkness (non-PoP mobs I cast splurt first and let pet eat aggro til darkness applied) and you don't have to wait for spells to wear off, you can tell how far in you are by the damage.<br /><br />Using dots to time snare is THE BEST way imo.  I always forget to look at my timer when I cast, then I'm playing the guessing game which will get you killed.<br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Sayleth</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/18/2003&nbsp;: 11:22:52 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I love SCS, and it definitely works on DoTs.  If you dont think that it does test a duplicate spell lineup with another on a raid.  The guy without SCS is going to get summoned first everytime, at least with SCS3 vs no SCS at all.  Its well worth it IMO.  As good as scm or nd?  No, but for a raiding/grouping necro I would say its worth getting in your first 100 points for sure.<br /><br />The only downside to SCS at all is that you lose something for aggro kiting.  Now, if you have BoT you lost nothing.  Snare+BoT keeps aggro from your pet 100% of the time, even if it has Mage weps and max haste.   If you dont have BoT, and you aggro kite, then I would say forgo SCS because keeping aggro is harder, but I found that Cor canceled out SCS3 fairly well.<br /><br />The main reason why BoT aggros like a motherfucker is because of the poison counters it adds to a mob.  Mobs dont like counters, and they must dislike Poison counters even more than disease counters.  SOE is aware of this problem, they choose to do nothing about it at this time.<br /><br />BoT is roughly the same aggro as Tash, so if you really want to be safe, wait until you see an enchanter Tash and you are gtg, at least for the first cast.<br /><br />Sayleth</span></font></td>
              </tr>
