              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Deslegrate</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/17/2003&nbsp;: 11:16:14 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I've only been using BoT for about a month now, so not as long as some people, but 85-90% of that time has been in Bastion of Thunder EXP groups.<br /><br />Pal/SK tank = SK followed by BoT. (didnt have FP then, do now)<br /><br />Just remember that AFTER you cast BoT even with a pal tank, FD before you sit.  You will be fine.  Same goes for SK tank.<br /><br />War tank..... Totally different story.  I would get summoned at 70% casting.  Which is kinda sad.  So if your tank is a War, you might want to use FP (i heard its much lower aggro, just got it other day so dont really know yet).<br /><br />Aggro kiting, is absolutely, positivly, cake with BoT.  I was duo'ing HOH for kicks with a random Rogue.  Second tick into BoT, nothing will out aggro you.<br /><br />ED<br />PE<br />RoD<br />BoT<br />SK<br />DP or FS<br />SoS or Pyro<br />DP(death peace)<br /><br />That is my aggro kite set up. <br /><br />Grats on BoT, its awesome.  The damage it does, in the time it lasts is just plain awesome.  <br /><br />I dont know how your getting summoned on raids or was it elemental planes exp?  Either way, I'm guessing you had a war tank.  If it was EXP and you had a Pal or SK, then bitch slap them, theres no reason they should lose aggro to you.  At least not that often, freak aggro loss or gain does happen with everyone.<br /><br /><br />ADD - Just a little extra info, if your groups tank is a war, YOU will get summoned almost always.  At least I do.  Just keep FS memmed, its more then good enough to buy time to FD, and after you cast BoT move finger immediately to FD hotkey.  Any dmg that leaks through FS, you will recoup fast with SK.  Just make sure SK is always up, so you dont mana suck the cleric. (I feel like a failure when the cleric has to resort to healing me - and no, i dont die often, even with 6 hours with a war tank, I dont die.) And I've tried casting at 60%, 70%, 80%.  Summoned even at 60% most of the time, and you dont get full effect of DoT at that point anyway, at lesat 1 or 2 ticks will be wasted.  So don't be afraid to lay it out, just make sure FS is fresh (each time you get hit and dont lose it, click it off between pulls and REUP it).  <br /><br />Don't be afraid to click off FS between pulls and reup it.  Just keep a good DPS per fight, and with our mana regen we are not gods.  Don't nuke when theres no need, just cause we have good mana regen.  (FP/SK/BoT + Pet = PLENTY of DPS) IF you can keep that up each fight, which you can, your DPS will be 135ish.  Not counting your pet which with a tank who knows positioning and rogue, will be 50-60ish easy.  So your looking at 180+ DPS per fight, every fight.  Only extra mana you should spend is on FD/FS.  Rest of it is wasted mana.  (yes your 1300dmg neuro for 460 raw mana is WASTED mana. Don't care, its a waste, ratio sucks, and its not needed, want to nuke go play a wiz or mage or druid.)<br /><br />Only change this spell needs is a higher resist adjust.  This spell should be at the very least -100.  I would even say it should be -200.  But thats just my opinion on that.<br /><br /></span></font></td>
